The United States prioritizes the security of all weapons-usable nuclear material used for military purposes. They have implemented various measures to ensure the safety, security, and control of military materials. These measures include reducing and eliminating nuclear weapons, disposing of excess materials, and consolidating materials across the nuclear security enterprise. The United States also has criteria and standards for protecting military materials, accounting and control processes, personnel reliability programs, training and certification programs, and performance assessments. They also have weapon design features that prevent unauthorized detonation and actively protect against tampering. The United States recognizes the cyber threat to nuclear material control systems and collaborates with industry partners to develop security solutions. They report on the security of military material and publicly outline their long-term security plans. Additionally, the United States is focused on strengthening the security culture within the nuclear enterprise through various initiatives.